# Onboarding Flow Design Overhaul

## Context

The signup/login pages have a polished editorial design (warm cream, gold accents, Playfair Display typography, morphing blobs). But the **profile setup modal** uses a cold dark navy (`rgb(4,20,29)`) with no CSS variables, and the **welcome message** is a plain white card with a generic party popper SVG. These three consecutive screens feel like three different apps. This plan harmonizes them into one cohesive editorial flow.

## Files to Modify

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `client/src/components/HomePage/home.css` | Restyle profile editor: replace hardcoded colors with CSS variables, match auth page design |
| `client/src/components/HomePage/Home.jsx` | Update title/copy, add placeholders, color-coded username feedback |
| `client/src/components/WelcomeMessage/welcomemessage.css` | Full rewrite: CSS variables, dark mode, remove duplicate @media blocks |
| `client/src/components/WelcomeMessage/WelcomeMessage.jsx` | Replace party popper with pen icon, add "Begin writing" CTA, update copy |

## Change 1: Profile Setup Modal (home.css + Home.jsx)

### CSS — Replace hardcoded navy with warm editorial theme

- `.profile-editor`: `rgb(4,20,29)` -> `var(--bg-card)` + `var(--border-card)` + `var(--shadow-modal)`. Change from `width:50%; height:90%` to `max-width:440px; height:auto` (matches auth-form-card pattern)
- `.profile-editor-bg`: `rgba(141,141,141,0.2)` -> `var(--bg-backdrop-heavy)`, increase blur to 8px
- `.edit-profile-title-container`: Add `font-family: "Playfair Display"`, use `var(--text-heading)`
- `.save-bttn` / `.save-bttn-disabled`: Match `.primary-button` from signup (dark bg, hover lift, disabled opacity)
- `.edit-profile-name-input` / `.edit-profile-bio-input`: Match `.auth-input` from signup — `var(--bg-primary)`, `var(--border-card)`, gold focus ring (`box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(212,168,83,0.12)`)
- `.input-title`: Match label style from signup — uppercase, `var(--text-muted)`, `0.7rem`
- `.input-title-container`: Change to `justify-content: space-between` (label left, counter right)
- `.name-input-container` / `.bio-input-container`: Remove border wrapper, use gap layout
- `.profile-edit-container`: Remove hardcoded navy background
- Add `@keyframes slideUp` (same as signup.css) for the card entrance
- Remove hardcoded `color: rgb(255,255,255) !important` from mobile @media blocks
- Add username status classes: `.username-status-available` (green), `.username-status-taken` (red), `.username-status-checking` (muted)
- Add dark mode overrides for elevated inputs

### JSX — Welcoming copy + username feedback

- Title: "Edit profile" -> "Welcome to Iskrib"
- Add subtitle: `<p className="setup-subtitle">Set up your writing identity.</p>`
- Add `placeholder="Your name"` on name input
- Add `placeholder="A few words about you..."` on bio textarea
- Username status: apply color classes + prepend checkmark/X unicode chars
- Save button: show "Saving..." text during upload, disable during upload

## Change 2: Welcome Message (welcomemessage.css + WelcomeMessage.jsx)

### CSS — Full rewrite

- `.welcome-message-container`: `position: fixed`, `var(--bg-backdrop-heavy)`, blur 6px
- `.welcome-message-child-container`: `var(--bg-card)`, `var(--border-card)`, `var(--shadow-modal)`, `max-width: 400px`, `border-radius: 16px`
- Remove the 54px square close icon -> small 32px circular close button top-right (`.welcome-close-btn`)
- Add `.welcome-heading`: Playfair Display, `var(--text-heading)`
- `.welcome-message`: Lora serif, italic, `var(--text-body)`
- `.iskrib-word`: Playfair Display, `var(--accent-amber)`, bold
- Add `.welcome-cta`: Full-width button matching `.primary-button` (dark bg, hover lift)
- Add `.welcome-icon`: `var(--accent-amber)` for the pen icon
- Dark mode: gold CTA button, stronger shadow
- **Remove duplicate @media blocks** (lines 56-77 and 79-100 were identical)
- Single responsive block at 480px

### JSX — Editorial design

- Replace 80px party popper SVG (100+ lines) with 48px Material pen/edit icon (single path, `currentColor`)
- Add heading: `<h2 className="welcome-heading">You're all set</h2>`
- Update message: "Your thoughts now have a home on **Iskrib**. The blank page awaits."
- Add CTA: `<button className="welcome-cta">Begin writing</button>` (calls `onClose`)
- Add small X close button top-right (aria-labeled)
- Confetti colors: brand palette `['#D4A853', '#C4943E', '#E0BA6A', '#FAF9F6', '#8A9E7A']` instead of rainbow
- Softer animation: `scale: 0.95, y: 12` initial instead of `scale: 0` (gentle reveal vs popping from nothing)

## Visual Consistency After Changes

| Screen | Background | Card | Typography | Accent |
|--------|-----------|------|------------|--------|
| Signup | `--bg-primary` | `--bg-card` + `--shadow-card-sm` | Playfair + Lora + Outfit | Gold focus rings |
| Profile Setup | `--bg-backdrop-heavy` | `--bg-card` + `--shadow-modal` | Playfair + Lora + Outfit | Gold focus rings |
| Welcome | `--bg-backdrop-heavy` | `--bg-card` + `--shadow-modal` | Playfair + Lora + Outfit | Gold icon + confetti |

All three screens now share the same warm editorial card pattern.

## Implementation Order

1. `home.css` — Profile editor CSS overhaul (highest impact)
2. `Home.jsx` — Title, placeholders, username feedback
3. `welcomemessage.css` — Full rewrite
4. `WelcomeMessage.jsx` — SVG, CTA, copy

## Verification

1. Start the dev server (`npm run dev` in client/)
2. Create a new account via `/signUp`
3. Verify the profile setup modal matches the editorial design (warm bg, gold focus rings, Playfair title)
4. Verify username field shows green "Available" / red "Taken" with icons
5. After saving, verify welcome message has pen icon, gold confetti, "Begin writing" CTA
6. Toggle dark mode and verify all three screens adapt properly
7. Test at mobile width (< 480px) — modal should be ~92% width
